---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Legal Terms - Quasar Contact"
  description="Privacy Policy and Legal Terms for Quasar Contact secure messaging platform. GDPR compliant data protection information."
>
<div class="main-content page-content">
  <div class="container inner">
    <div class="page-header">
      <h2>Legal Terms & Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p class="page-subtitle">Your privacy and data protection rights</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-content">
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

        <div class='space'>
        <h3>Data Controller</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Artem Turlenko</strong><br />
          Email: artem.turlenko@quasar.contact
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class='space'>
        <h3>Data I Collect</h3>
        <p>
          When you create an account on quasar.contact, I store your email
          address to enable user identification and account access. This is
          the only personal data I collect and store.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class='space'>
        <h3>Purpose of Data Processing</h3>
        <p>Your email address is used exclusively to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide access to your account</li>
          <li>Distinguish between different users</li>
          <li>Enable secure authentication</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          I do not share your data with third parties, use it for marketing
          purposes, or analyze it for any commercial purposes.
        </p>
        </div>
        <div class='space'>
        <h3>Legal Basis</h3>
        <p>
          Data processing is carried out in accordance with Art. 6 Para. 1
          lit. b GDPR (contract fulfillment) and Art. 6 Para. 1 lit. f GDPR
          (legitimate interests in providing secure communication services).
        </p>
        </div>
        <div class='space'>
        <h3>Data Retention</h3>
        <p>
          Your data is stored as long as you maintain an account with me.
          When you delete your account, all personal data is permanently
          removed from my systems within 30 days.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class='space'>
        <h3>Your Rights</h3>
        <p>Under GDPR, you have the following rights:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Right of Access:</strong> Request information about your
            stored data
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to Rectification:</strong> Correct inaccurate
            personal data
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to Erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your
            personal data
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to Restriction:</strong> Limit processing of your
            data
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to Data Portability:</strong> Receive your data in
            a structured format
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to Object:</strong> Object to processing of your
            personal data
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Right to Lodge a Complaint:</strong> File a complaint
            with a supervisory authority
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class='space'>
        <h3>Hosting and Data Location</h3>
        <p>
          My website and services are hosted on cloud infrastructure
          providers. Servers may be located outside the EU. I ensure
          appropriate safeguards are in place for international data
          transfers in compliance with GDPR requirements.
        </p>
      </div>
      
        <h3>Security Measures</h3>
        <p>
          I implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to
          protect your personal data:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>End-to-end encryption for all messages</li>
          <li>Secure authentication mechanisms</li>
          <li>Regular security updates and monitoring</li>
          <li>Limited access to personal data on a need-to-know basis</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Terms of Service</h2>
        <div class='space'>
        <h3>Service Description</h3>
        <p>
          Quasar Contact provides end-to-end encrypted messaging services.
          The service is currently in alpha stage and features may change
          without notice.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class='space'>
        <h3>User Responsibilities</h3>
        <p>By using my service, you agree to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use the service in compliance with applicable laws</li>
          <li>Not use the service for illegal activities</li>
          <li>Maintain the security of your account credentials</li>
          <li>Report security vulnerabilities responsibly</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class='space'>
        <h3>Service Availability</h3>
        <p>
          While I strive for high availability, I do not guarantee
          uninterrupted service. The service is provided "as is" during the
          alpha stage.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class='space'>
        <h3>Limitation of Liability</h3>
        <p>
          My liability is limited to the extent permitted by applicable law.
          I am not liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential
          damages.
        </p>
      </div>
        <h3>Changes to Terms</h3>
        <p>
          I may update these terms from time to time. Users will be notified
          of significant changes via email or through the application.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Cookie Policy</h2>
        <div class='space'>
        <h3>What Are Cookies</h3>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files stored on your device to help improve
          your experience and enable certain functionality.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class='space'>
        <h3>Cookies I Use</h3>
        <p>I use the following types of cookies:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Required for basic
            functionality and security
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Preference Cookies:</strong> Remember your settings and
            preferences
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> Help us understand how you
            use our service (anonymized)
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
        <h3>Managing Cookies</h3>
        <p>
          You can control cookies through your browser settings. However,
          disabling certain cookies may affect the functionality of my
          service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Contact Information</h2>
        <p>
          For any questions regarding these terms, privacy policy, or your
          data protection rights, please contact:
        </p>
        <div class="contact-info">
          <p>
            <strong>Artem Turlenko</strong><br />
            Email: artem.turlenko@quasar.contact<br />
            Subject: Data Protection / Privacy Inquiry
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="legal-footer">
        <p>Last updated: June 21, 2025.This policy will be updated if there are any changes to my data
          processing practices.</p>
      
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</BaseLayout>